    Calculations
    public static enum Calculations.FileReaderState
extends java.lang.Enum<Calculations.FileReaderState>
    The states the file reader can be in

    Default state:
    Begining

    First stage states:
    Operator
    EOF

    Operator states:
    Plus
    Minus
    Divide
    Multiply
    Assign
    Print
    LineFeed

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant Description
      Assign
      The operation is Assignment and the value to be added will be parsed and passed to the tabulator for assignment
      Begining
      The state the FSM will be in before any of the file is read
      Divide
      The operation is Division and the value to be added will be parsed and passed to the tabulator for calculation
      EOF
      The FSM is at the EOF and is done parsing
      LineFeed
      The operation is LineFeed the remainder of the line will be discarded and the tabulator will be requested to preform a linefeed
      Minus
      The operation is Subtraction and the value to be added will be parsed and passed to the tabulator for calculation
      Multiply
      The operation is Multiplication and the value to be added will be parsed and passed to the tabulator for calculation
      Operator
      In this state the FSM is looking for an operator or the EOF marker
      Plus
      The operation is addition and the value to be added will be parsed and passed to the tabulator for calculation
      Print
      The operation is Printing the remainder of the line will be discarded and the tabulator will be requested to draw
